PART 2
1 Section 5.2010. To the Office of Administration

CCS SS SCS HCS HB 2005 33
2 In reference to all sections of Part 1 of this act:
3 No funds appropriated in this act shall be expended by the Office
4 of Administration for major hardware refreshes, expansion of
5 state-operated data center infrastructure, or development of new
6 custom on-premise applications unless the department, in
7 coordination with the Information Technology Services Division,
8 obtains the services of (an) independent third-party vendor(s) to
9 conduct an evaluation and develop a comprehensive plan for the
10 possible transition of the state’s information technology
11 operations from a capital expenditure model to an operational
12 expenditure model. Such expenditures and plans shall be
13 reviewed first by the House Budget Committee Chair and
14 Ranking Member and the Senate Appropriations Chair and
15 Ranking Member and then reviewed and approved through the
16 Cabinet IT Governance Council (CITGC). The Office of
17 Administration, in conjunction with the Information Technology
18 Services Division, shall establish a Chief Innovation and
19 Technology Officer, responsible for evaluating, coordinating,
20 and advancing modernization of state information technology
21 systems toward scalable, consumption-based service models,
22 including cloud, software-as-a-service, data, artificial
23 intelligence (AI), enterprise architecture, and financial
24 operations.
